<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JAN 93 / Haiti army backs talks
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PORT-AU-PRINCE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Haitian army announced yesterday it had agreed to UN-brokered
negotiations to advance democracy in the country, AP reports from
Port-au-Prince. It had also agreed to the appointment of an interim prime
minister, a UN official said.
The announcement followed delivery of a letter from exiled President
Jean-Bertrand Aristide in which he agreed to talk to coup supporters for the
first time since his overthrow in September 1991. It also followed calls by
US President-elect Bill Clinton for Haitians not to begin an exodus.
</TEXT>
