<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JAN 93 / Pensions change is proposed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government could increase tax revenues by Pounds 1bn a year by ending
the exemption to those who take a portion of their pension in a lump sum on
retirement, the Institute for Fiscal Studies, said yesterday in a report
financed by the National Association of Pension Funds.
But it said there was no case for substantial changes to the tax structure
for occupational pension funds. The government hopes to encourage people who
opt out of the state scheme to stay out of it until they reach retirement
age.
Taxation of Private Pensions. Institute for Fiscal Studies, 7 Ridgmount
Street, London WC1E 7AE. Pounds 10.
