<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JAN 93 / Powerful earthquake rocks Japan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A powerful earthquake measuring 7.5 on the Richter scale rocked northern
Japan yesterday, injuring at least 95 people but apparently causing only
minor damage, authorities said, Reuter reports from Tokyo. The tremor, the
strongest to hit Japan for almost 11 years, was felt across the country from
the Pacific coast to the Sea of Japan, the national meteorological agency
said.
