<HEADLINE>
FT  16 JAN 93 / Markets: European bond unit trust - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Barclays Unicorn is launching a new European Bond unit trust on Monday. It
will be the first onshore unit trust aiming for total return rather than
income to invest exclusively in European markets.
According to BZW Investment Management, which will manage the trust, the
high real yields available in Europe at present are attractive (see
accompanying graph), and there is a hope of capital gain if yields converge
towards German levels. The capital value of the fund should also benefit
from cuts in German base rates, if and when they happen.
Minimum investment is Pounds 1,000, or Pounds 30 per month. Initial charge
is 3.5 per cent (with a 1 per cent discount during the offer period which
lasts until January 29), and annual charges are 0.75 per cent.
Income is distributed in March and September, and the projected initial
yield is 3.5 per cent.
