Mr McCarthy also announced that, to achieve a more equal distribution of the
trading results for the two halves of the year, the Dublin-based group was
changing to a January year end.
To achieve this change, Ryan Hotels would be reporting on a 15-month period
from November 1991 to January 1993. At this stage the question of a final
dividend would be considered, the chairman said. A final of 0.5p was paid
last time.
