   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Quebec Court of Appeal, in a test case, has upheld a federal government
ban on tobacco advertising, ruling that it does not violate freedom of
expression under the constitution, writes Robert Gibbens in Montreal.
A lower court had found the ban unconstitutional and the federal government
had appealed. The tobacco industry, which has complied with the federal ban
since 1989, said it would almost certainly take the case to the Supreme
Court of Canada. The three big tobacco producers seeking a final ruling on
the ban are led by Imasco, the Canadian arm of BAT Industries.
